### Hadith 1:90

*Narrated Abu Mas'ud Al-Ansari:*

Once a man said to Allah's Apostle "O Allah's Apostle! I may not attend
the (compulsory congregational) prayer because so and so (the Imam)
prolongs the prayer when he leads us for it. The narrator added: "I
never saw the Prophet more furious in giving advice than he was on that
day. The Prophet said, "O people! Some of you make others dislike good
deeds (the prayers). So whoever leads the people in prayer should
shorten it because among them there are the sick the weak and the needy
(having some jobs to do)."

